AVIAN INFLUENZA (35): CHINA (TIBET)
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Sun 19 Apr 2009
Source: Xinhua [edited]
<http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2009-04/19/content_7692796.htm>


China confirms bird flu outbreak in Lhasa
-------------------------------------------
China's Ministry of Agriculture (MOA) confirmed Sunday [19 Apr 2009]
a new outbreak of bird flu in Lhasa, southwestern Tibet Autonomous
Region. The national bird flu laboratory confirmed that the H5N1 bird
flu virus was found in poultry sold at a poultry wholesale market in
Chengguan District of Lhasa on 12 Apr 2009.

Emergency measures have been taken and the epidemic has been brought
under control, the MOA said in a brief notice, and 1679 fowl were
culled after the outbreak. According to the local health department,
no abnormalities were found among people in contact with the poultry,
the ministry said.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Dan Silver

[For Lhasa's location, see
<http://healthmap.org/promed/en?name=Lhasa,%20China&g=6301884&v=29.667,91.133,5>.
- Mod.AS]
